description.narrative:
This initiative covers the design of the new Indonesia Infrastructure Program. The proposed infrastructure program will align with the long-term objectives of the infrastructure sector delivery strategy, to support rapid, sustainable and inclusive economic growth and improved access to basic infrastructure services to help reduce poverty. Assistance will be structured around the following three long-term outcomes: 
a)	An improved policy and regulatory framework conducive to infrastructure development: This outcome will help address the uncertain and inconsistent regulatory environment which has held back public and private infrastructure investment;
b)	High quality planning, coordination and project preparation: This outcome will help address underinvestment in the infrastructure sector as well as improve the overall sustainability of infrastructure investments by facilitating high-quality project designs;
c)	High quality project delivery, management and maintenance by Government: This
